Time|GMT]] ([[UTC+00]])\n|home={{ru-rt|NZL}}\n|score=[[2015 Rugby World Cup knockout stage#Final: New Zealand vs Australia|34\u201317]]\n|report=[http://www.rugbyworldcup.com/news/121138 Report]\n|away={{ru|AUS}}\n|try1=[[Nehe Milner-Skudder|Milner-Skudder]] 39' c<br />[[Ma'a Nonu|Nonu]] 42' m<br />[[Beauden Barrett|Barrett]] 79' c\n|con1=[[Dan Carter|Carter]] (2/3) 40', 80'\n|pen1=[[Dan Carter|Carter]] (4/4) 8', 27', 36', 75'\n|drop1=[[Dan Carter|Carter]] 70'\n|try2=[[David Pocock|Pocock]] 53' c<br />[[Tevita Kuridrani|Kuridrani]] 64' c\n|con2=[[Bernard Foley|Foley]] (2/2) 54', 65'\n|pen2=[[Bernard Foley|Foley]] (1/1) 14'\n|stadium=[[Twickenham Stadium]], [[London]]\n|attendance=80,125\n|referee=[[Nigel Owens]] ([[Welsh Rugby Union|Wales]])\n}}\n\n==Awards==\nAt the 2015 [[World Rugby Awards]], Japan's game-winning final try against South Africa was named the best match moment of the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |title=World Rugby Awards Past Winners |url=https://www.world.rugby/awards/past-winners |publisher=World Rugby |date=9 November 2014 |accessdate=11 July 2019 }}</ref> A dream team was named made up of the best performing players of the tournament.<ref>[http://dreamteam.rugbyworldcup.com/ Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 G\u00e9n\u00e9rale Rugby World Cup 2015 dream team] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160522210120/http://dreamteam.rugbyworldcup.com/ |date=22 May 2016 }}</ref>\n\n'''2015 Rugby World Cup dream team'''<ref>{{cite tweet |user=RugbyFifteen |number=660960457759571969 |date=1 November 2015 |title=@SocieteGenerale #RWC2015 Dream Team #WorldRugbyAwards |access-date=11 July 2019 }}</ref>\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n{| cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"\n|-\n!width=\"30\"|Pos.\n!width=\"30\"|\n!width=\"210\"|Player\n|-\n|FB ||'''15'''||{{flagicon|JPN}} [[Ayumu Goromaru]]\n|-\n|RW ||'''14'''||{{flagicon|NZL}} [[Nehe Milner-Skudder]]\n|-\n|OC ||'''13'''||{{flagicon|NZL}} [[Conrad Smith]]\n|-\n|IC ||'''12'''||{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Matt Giteau]]\n|-\n|LW ||'''11'''||{{flagicon|NZL}} [[Julian Savea]]\n|-\n|FH ||'''10'''||{{flagicon|NZL}} [[Dan Carter]]\n|-\n|SH ||'''9''' ||{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Greig Laidlaw]]\n|-\n|}\n{{col-break|gap=1em}}\n{| style=\"font-size:100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"\n|-\n!width=\"30\"|Pos.\n!width=\"30\"|\n!width=\"210\"|Player\n|-\n|N8 ||'''8''' ||{{flagicon|AUS}} [[David Pocock]]\n|-\n|OF ||'''7''' ||{{flagicon|RSA}} [[Schalk Burger]]\n|-\n|BF ||'''6''' ||{{flagicon|GEO}} [[Mamuka Gorgodze]]\n|-\n|RL ||'''5''' ||{{flagicon|FIJ}} [[Leone Nakarawa]]\n|-\n|LL ||'''4''' ||{{flagicon|RSA}} [[Eben Etzebeth]]\n|-\n|TP ||'''3''' ||{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Ramiro Herrera]]\n|-\n|HK ||'''2''' ||{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Stephen Moore (rugby union)|Stephen Moore]]\n|-\n|LP ||'''1''' ||{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Marcos Ayerza]]\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Statistics==\n{{main article|2015 Rugby World Cup statistics}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;float:right\"\n|-\n|+ Most points \n|-\n! style=\"width:7em\"|Player\n! style=\"width:7em\"|Team\n! style=\"width:2em\"|Points\n|-\n|align=left|[[Nicol\u00e1s S\u00e1nchez (rugby union)|Nicol\u00e1s S\u00e1nchez]]\n|align=left|{{ru|ARG}}\n|97\n|-\n|align=left|[[Handr\u00e9 Pollard]]\n|align=left|{{ru|RSA}}\n|93\n|-\n|align=left|[[Bernard Foley]]\n|align=left|{{ru|AUS}}\n|82\n|-\n|align=left|[[Dan Carter]]\n|align=left|{{ru|NZL}}\n|82\n|-\n|align=left|[[Greig Laidlaw]]\n|align=left|{{ru|SCO}}\n|79\n|}\n\nThe tournament's top point scorer was Argentine fly-half [[Nicol\u00e1s S\u00e1nchez (rugby union)|Nicol\u00e1s S\u00e1nchez]], who scored 97 points.<ref>{{cite news|title=S\u00e1nchez is World Cup Top Points Scorer|url=http://www.americasrugbynews.com/2015/11/01/sanchez-is-world-cup-top-points-scorer/|accessdate=1 November 2015|publisher=Americas Rugby|date=1 November 2015}}</ref> \nNew Zealand wing [[Julian Savea]] scored the most tries, eight, equalling the record for one tournament set by his compatriot [[Jonah Lomu]] and South African [[Bryan Habana]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Cueto|first=Mark|authorlink=Mark Cueto|title=Bryan Habana and Julian Savea can light up epic Rugby World Cup semifinal|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/rugby/story/_/id/13949147/mark-cueto-bryan-habana-julian-savea-light-epic-semifinal|accessdate=1 November 2015|publisher=ESPN|date=23 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Match officials==\nWorld Rugby named the following twelve referees, seven assistant referees and four television match officials to handle the pool stage games:<ref name=\"Officials\">{{cite web|url=http://www.worldrugby.org/news/65914|date=7 April 2015|accessdate=7 April 2015|work=worldrugby.com|publisher=[[World Rugby]]|title=Match officials announced for Rugby World Cup 2015}}</ref>\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n;Referees\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Wayne Barnes]] <small>([[Rugby Football Union|England]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|IRE|rugby union}} [[George Clancy (rugby)|George Clancy]] <small>([[Irish Rugby Football Union|Ireland]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[JP Doyle]] <small>([[Rugby Football Union|England]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[J\u00e9r\u00f4me Garc\u00e8s]] <small>([[French Rugby Federation|France]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Pascal Ga\u00fcz\u00e8re]] <small>([[French Rugby Federation|France]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|NZL}} [[Glen Jackson (rugby union)|Glen Jackson]] <small>([[New Zealand Rugby Union|New Zealand]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|RSA}} [[Craig Joubert]] <small>([[South African Rugby Union|South Africa]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|IRE|rugby union}} [[John Lacey (rugby union)|John Lacey]] <small>([[Irish Rugby Football Union|Ireland]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|WAL}} [[Nigel Owens]] <small>([[Welsh Rugby Union|Wales]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|RSA}} [[Jaco Peyper]] <small>([[South African Rugby Union|South Africa]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Romain Poite]] <small>([[French Rugby Federation|France]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|NZL}} [[Chris Pollock]] <small>([[New Zealand Rugby Union|New Zealand]])</small>\n\n{{col-2}}\n;Assistant referees\n*{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Federico Anselmi]] <small>([[Argentine Rugby Union|Argentina]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|RSA}} [[Stuart Berry]] <small>([[South African Rugby Union|South Africa]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|NZL}} [[Mike Fraser (rugby referee)|Mike Fraser]] <small>([[New Zealand Rugby Union|New Zealand]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Angus Gardner]] <small>([[Australian Rugby Union|Australia]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|WAL}} [[Leighton Hodges]] <small>([[Welsh Rugby Union|Wales]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Marius Mitrea]] <small>([[Italian Rugby Federation|Italy]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Mathieu Raynal]] <small>([[French Rugby Federation|France]])</small>\n\n;Television match officials\n*{{flagicon|AUS}} [[George Ayoub]] <small>([[Australian Rugby Union|Australia]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} Graham Hughes <small>([[Rugby Football Union|England]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|NZL}} Ben Skeen <small>([[New Zealand Rugby Union|New Zealand]])</small>\n*{{flagicon|RSA}} Shaun Veldsman <small>([[South African Rugby Union|South Africa]])</small>\n{{Col-end}}\n\n==Media coverage==\n[[ITV Sport]] was the UK and worldwide host broadcaster for the 2015 event, having signed a deal in 2011 to broadcast the 2011 and 2015 RWC tournaments. ITV won the rights after outbidding rivals including the [[BBC]] and [[Sky Sports]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/7914793/ITV-secures-television-rights-to-2011-and-2015-Rugby-Union-World-Cups.html |title=ITV secures television rights to 2011 and 2015 Rugby Union World Cups |date=28 July 2010 |work=Daily Telegraph |accessdate=4 December 2012 |location=London |first=Gavin |last=Mairs}}</ref> It showed every match from the tournament live in the UK on ITV or ITV4.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://stakeholders.ofcom.org.uk/broadcasting/broadcast-codes/code-sports-events/approved/rugby-15-statement |title=Rugby World Cup 2015 - Statement |publisher=Ofcom |date=3 September 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151101115211/http://stakeholders.ofcom.org.uk/broadcasting/broadcast-codes/code-sports-events/approved/rugby-15-statement |archivedate=1 November 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%\"\n|-\n!width=15%|Country or region\n!width=21%|Broadcaster\n!width=64%|Broadcasting\n|-\n|Africa<sup>1</sup>\n|[[SuperSport (TV channel)|SuperSport]]<ref name=\"RWC Where to watch?\"/><ref name=\"totalsportek.com\" />\n|All 48 matches broadcast live\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Argentina\n|[[ESPN Latin America|ESPN Extra]]\n|All 48 matches broadcast live.\n|-\n|[[TV P\u00fablica Digital (Argentina)|TV P\u00fablica]]\n|All Argentina matches, plus opening, semi-final and final matches.\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Australia\n|[[Fox Sports (Australia)|Fox Sports]]<ref name=\"RWC Where to watch?\"/><ref name=\"totalsportek.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.totalsportek.com/rugby/tv-channels-broadcasting-2015-rugby-world-cup/|title=List of TV Channels Broadcasting 2015 Rugby World Cup Live|work=TOTAL SPORTEK}}</ref>\n|All 48 matches broadcast live<ref name=\"Rugby World Cup 2015 Live TV\">{{cite web|url=http://rugbyworldcuptv.com/|title=Rugby World Cup 2015 Live TV|date=8 April 2015|access-date=17 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150917193557/http://www.rugbyworldcuptv.com/|archive-date=17 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Nine Network]]<ref name=\"RWC Where to watch?\"/><ref name=\"totalsportek.com\" />\n|All Australian matches, some other pool games and all knockout games free-to-air live\n|-\n|Azerbaijan<br />Turkey\n|[[Tivibu Spor]]\n|45 matches live (excluding Tonga v Georgia, Wales v Fiji and France v Canada at the pool stage)\n|-\n|Brazil\n|[[ESPN Brasil]]<ref name=\"RWC Where to watch?\"/><ref name=\"SouthAmerica\"/>\n|All 48 matches broadcast live \n|-\n|rowspan=2|Canada\n|[[The Sports Network|TSN]]<ref name=\"RWC Where to watch?\"/><ref name=\"TSN/RDS\">{{cite web|url=http://www2.tsn.ca/story/?id=372115|title=WORLD CUP OF RUGBY COMING TO TSN I